'''Thomas Dachser''' (13 March 1906 in [[Haldenwang]] (near [[Günzburg]]) - 11 April 1979 in [[Munich]]) was a German businessman. In 1930, he founded the forwarding agency [[Dachser]] in Kempten in the Allgäu.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=11x-Y0cdFbcC|title=International Logistics and Supply Chain Outsourcing: From Local to Global|last=Rushton|first=Alan|date=2007-06-03|publisher=Kogan Page Publishers|isbn=9780749452124|page=157|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iA67AAAAIAAJ|title=International Directory of Company Histories|last=Grant|first=Tina|date=2007-09-01|publisher=ST JAMES Press|isbn=9781558625921|pages=57-59|language=en}}</ref> Today the business, still owned by the family, is one of the largest logistics service providers in Europe. In 1977, Thomas Dachser was awarded the [[Bavarian Order of Merit]] by the then prime minister of Bavaria [[Alfons Goppel]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Members of the Bavarian Order of Merit|url = http://www.celebrityillustratedmagazine.com/q/Members_of_the_Bavarian_Order_of_Merit|website = Celebrity|accessdate = 2015-10-05|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151006071659/http://www.celebrityillustratedmagazine.com/q/Members_of_the_Bavarian_Order_of_Merit|archivedate = 2015-10-06|df = }}</ref>

